## 

<span key="3f00fb89704d41a68cb58199d3cc6021"><span offset-key="3f00fb89704d41a68cb58199d3cc6021:0">Introduction</span></span>

<span key="c875a753b64f4124ae5d299842ec27a7"><span offset-key="c875a753b64f4124ae5d299842ec27a7:0">The OpenAPI Specification (OAS) defines a standard, language-agnostic interface to RESTful APIs which allows both humans and computers to discover and understand the capabilities of the service without access to source code, documentation, or through network traffic inspection. When properly defined, a consumer can understand and interact with the remote service with a minimal amount of implementation logic.</span></span>

<span key="d6112b0aa26441219d660e65f9c791fc"><span offset-key="d6112b0aa26441219d660e65f9c791fc:0">An OpenAPI definition can then be used by documentation generation tools to display the API, code generation tools to generate servers and clients in various programming languages, testing tools, and many other use cases.</span></span>

## 

<span key="ba7f60744caf4b148ca17b5bd8bf76ad"><span offset-key="ba7f60744caf4b148ca17b5bd8bf76ad:0">Definitions</span></span>

<span key="65ec91459a5140d3aa6f017f414db699">**OpenAPI Document**</span>

<span key="7471740b495642478f3b18a172a6f02f"><span offset-key="7471740b495642478f3b18a172a6f02f:0">A document (or set of documents) that defines or describes an API. An OpenAPI definition uses and conforms to the OpenAPI Specification.</span></span>

<span key="40ce8fc5aac04fb2915942883016177b">**Path Templating**</span>

<span key="5dbe6c743050440c868b9122e1959db4"><span offset-key="5dbe6c743050440c868b9122e1959db4:0">Path templating refers to the usage of template expressions, delimited by curly braces ({}), to mark a section of a URL path as replaceable using path parameters.</span></span>

<span key="6d693d2d1dff4e74bb4cd0112297407f"><span offset-key="6d693d2d1dff4e74bb4cd0112297407f:0">Each template expression in the path MUST correspond to a path parameter that is included in the </span></span><a href="https://swagger.io/specification/#path-item-object" class="css-4rbku5 css-1dbjc4n r-1loqt21 r-1471scf r-1otgn73 r-1i6wzkk r-lrvibr"><span data-key="7698a8de21ed4335aebae83d5841509c" data-rnw-int-class="nearest_257-34236_259-34237-237__"><span data-key="0a5ca339ed70473a96f4915b85478a10"><span data-offset-key="0a5ca339ed70473a96f4915b85478a10:0">Path Item</span></span></span></a><span key="b223c993010846aaa40ae7a1968b4cbb"><span offset-key="b223c993010846aaa40ae7a1968b4cbb:0"> itself and/or in each of the Path Item's </span></span><a href="https://swagger.io/specification/#operation-object" class="css-4rbku5 css-1dbjc4n r-1loqt21 r-1471scf r-1otgn73 r-1i6wzkk r-lrvibr"><span data-key="c5a586729b00425fb0f46aee499ec88b" data-rnw-int-class="nearest_257-34236_259-34237-237__"><span data-key="d9a0891940b04346ac9d2f5bdb88d91a"><span data-offset-key="d9a0891940b04346ac9d2f5bdb88d91a:0">Operations</span></span></span></a><span key="93e8824d3a964753b7864a8fb0c048a4"><span offset-key="93e8824d3a964753b7864a8fb0c048a4:0">.</span></span>

<span key="f97c0e7ca01148d0a25cd622a15d11c2">**Media Types**</span>

<span key="9b4d8a93b65d4771b96ed20c70ab011a"><span offset-key="9b4d8a93b65d4771b96ed20c70ab011a:0">Media type definitions are spread across several resources. The media type definitions SHOULD be in compliance with </span></span><a href="https://tools.ietf.org/html/rfc6838" class="css-4rbku5 css-1dbjc4n r-1loqt21 r-1471scf r-1otgn73 r-1i6wzkk r-lrvibr"><span data-key="e70a0146e95848cf9312d52aa0461e85" data-rnw-int-class="nearest_257-34236_259-34237-237__"><span data-key="09be70dd668d45649707eb5f55e7318c"><span data-offset-key="09be70dd668d45649707eb5f55e7318c:0">RFC6838</span></span></span></a><span key="fa44e124256d4bb1b534818c6e04027d"><span offset-key="fa44e124256d4bb1b534818c6e04027d:0">.</span></span>

<span key="6f9b0bddec144a98836621c04a63e0d8"><span offset-key="6f9b0bddec144a98836621c04a63e0d8:0">Some examples of possible media type definitions:</span></span>

1

<span key="867d7ad94a98487392d3e1a01fbd3066"><span offset-key="867d7ad94a98487392d3e1a01fbd3066:0"> text/plain; charset=utf-8 application/json application/vnd.github+json application/vnd.github.v3+json application/vnd.github.v3.raw+json application/vnd.github.v3.text+json application/vnd.github.v3.html+json application/vnd.github.v3.full+json application/vnd.github.v3.diff application/vnd.github.v3.patch</span></span>

<img src="data:image/svg+xml;base64," class="r-h7gdob r-10ptun7 r-1vzi8xi" />

Copied!

<span key="65a2dd7ceeac4fc787e2e640cdabb6e0">**HTTP Status Codes**</span>

<span key="2d1e968549784c8c978dd68f96c52212"><span offset-key="2d1e968549784c8c978dd68f96c52212:0">The HTTP Status Codes are used to indicate the status of the executed operation. The available status codes are defined by </span></span><a href="https://tools.ietf.org/html/rfc7231#section-6" class="css-4rbku5 css-1dbjc4n r-1loqt21 r-1471scf r-1otgn73 r-1i6wzkk r-lrvibr"><span data-key="18d1654b97904a5584934dffd9731268" data-rnw-int-class="nearest_257-34236_259-34237-237__"><span data-key="3f92dd62f12e45199b0c07091c381a3d"><span data-offset-key="3f92dd62f12e45199b0c07091c381a3d:0">RFC7231</span></span></span></a><span key="3bfc8b0c27e2463eb65e5b7c5ecb2341"><span offset-key="3bfc8b0c27e2463eb65e5b7c5ecb2341:0"> and registered status codes are listed in the </span></span><a href="https://www.iana.org/assignments/http-status-codes/http-status-codes.xhtml" class="css-4rbku5 css-1dbjc4n r-1loqt21 r-1471scf r-1otgn73 r-1i6wzkk r-lrvibr"><span data-key="ba3bd448ef464653be047c09d163c295" data-rnw-int-class="nearest_257-34236_259-34237-237__"><span data-key="97626b76c2eb4c769f55fafc3aac232c"><span data-offset-key="97626b76c2eb4c769f55fafc3aac232c:0">IANA Status Code Registry</span></span></span></a><span key="6d28fa8ce53b4766b50b132e564de6e4"><span offset-key="6d28fa8ce53b4766b50b132e564de6e4:0">.</span></span>

## 

<span key="fe837733ffe348d484ff0c585074acb5"><span offset-key="fe837733ffe348d484ff0c585074acb5:0">Specification</span></span>

### 

<span key="221a792e1ac14cb6a3eaecd476653075"><span offset-key="221a792e1ac14cb6a3eaecd476653075:0">Versions</span></span>

<span key="8073cfa62ddf4811b9ecdd9a2c2885bf"><span offset-key="8073cfa62ddf4811b9ecdd9a2c2885bf:0">The OpenAPI Specification is versioned using </span></span><a href="https://semver.org/spec/v2.0.0.html" class="css-4rbku5 css-1dbjc4n r-1loqt21 r-1471scf r-1otgn73 r-1i6wzkk r-lrvibr"><span data-key="0caafeab4c5e46708bcfa41947abff23" data-rnw-int-class="nearest_257-34236_259-34237-237__"><span data-key="3542c4ca772c433988a1733219d1167f"><span data-offset-key="3542c4ca772c433988a1733219d1167f:0">Semantic Versioning 2.0.0</span></span></span></a><span key="26d860d0234a4a2cb18da7b7b1dc6f3b"><span offset-key="26d860d0234a4a2cb18da7b7b1dc6f3b:0"> (semver) and follows the semver specification.</span></span>

<span key="c881da3d089a4ad3b6376b329e5416cc"><span offset-key="c881da3d089a4ad3b6376b329e5416cc:0">The </span>`major`<span offset-key="c881da3d089a4ad3b6376b329e5416cc:2">.</span>`minor`<span offset-key="c881da3d089a4ad3b6376b329e5416cc:4"> portion of the semver (for example </span>`3.0`<span offset-key="c881da3d089a4ad3b6376b329e5416cc:6">) SHALL designate the OAS feature set. Typically, </span>`.patch`<span offset-key="c881da3d089a4ad3b6376b329e5416cc:8"> versions address errors in this document, not the feature set. Tooling which supports OAS 3.0 SHOULD be compatible with all OAS 3.0.\* versions. The patch version SHOULD NOT be considered by tooling, making no distinction between </span>`3.0.0`<span offset-key="c881da3d089a4ad3b6376b329e5416cc:10"> and </span>`3.0.1`<span offset-key="c881da3d089a4ad3b6376b329e5416cc:12"> for example.</span></span>

<span key="6bc3ee2997974352b2b093b3f5de1a85"><span offset-key="6bc3ee2997974352b2b093b3f5de1a85:0">Each new minor version of the OpenAPI Specification SHALL allow any OpenAPI document that is valid against any previous minor version of the Specification, within the same major version, to be updated to the new Specification version with equivalent semantics. Such an update MUST only require changing the </span>`openapi`<span offset-key="6bc3ee2997974352b2b093b3f5de1a85:2"> property to the new minor version.</span></span>

<span key="bee47084a9304f6ba7e8bf170c800508"><span offset-key="bee47084a9304f6ba7e8bf170c800508:0">For example, a valid OpenAPI 3.0.2 document, upon changing its </span>`openapi`<span offset-key="bee47084a9304f6ba7e8bf170c800508:2"> property to </span>`3.1.0`<span offset-key="bee47084a9304f6ba7e8bf170c800508:4">, SHALL be a valid OpenAPI 3.1.0 document, semantically equivalent to the original OpenAPI 3.0.2 document. New minor versions of the OpenAPI Specification MUST be written to ensure this form of backward compatibility.</span></span>

<span key="ab5b3c2e23c944fe8bab7fc519ed85e7"><span offset-key="ab5b3c2e23c944fe8bab7fc519ed85e7:0">An OpenAPI document compatible with OAS 3.\*.\* contains a required </span></span><a href="https://swagger.io/specification/#oas-version" class="css-4rbku5 css-1dbjc4n r-1loqt21 r-1471scf r-1otgn73 r-1i6wzkk r-lrvibr"><span data-key="5833656a40314cd8a18778a9a460da9e" data-rnw-int-class="nearest_257-34236_259-34237-237__"><span data-key="96856a37e91346b89ab17f2eb861a166"><code class="r-1vckr1u r-z2wwpe r-uibjmv r-m2pi6t r-1hvjb8t" data-slate-leaf="true" data-offset-key="96856a37e91346b89ab17f2eb861a166:0">openapi</code></span></span></a><span key="27ffef2a812d41aaa4d13d0b888d792c"><span offset-key="27ffef2a812d41aaa4d13d0b888d792c:0"> field which designates the semantic version of the OAS that it uses. (OAS 2.0 documents contain a top-level version field named </span></span><a href="https://swagger.io/specification/versions/2.0.md#swagger-object" class="css-4rbku5 css-1dbjc4n r-1loqt21 r-1471scf r-1otgn73 r-1i6wzkk r-lrvibr"><span data-key="1e3aa09f79ed40cda191ca76269b6b8f" data-rnw-int-class="nearest_257-34236_259-34237-237__"><span data-key="f111f940508c48609cfe544a9707b55f"><code class="r-1vckr1u r-z2wwpe r-uibjmv r-m2pi6t r-1hvjb8t" data-slate-leaf="true" data-offset-key="f111f940508c48609cfe544a9707b55f:0">swagger</code></span></span></a><span key="2e69da27c0af4cf19da9835a01cfdef3"><span offset-key="2e69da27c0af4cf19da9835a01cfdef3:0"> and value </span>`"2.0"`<span offset-key="2e69da27c0af4cf19da9835a01cfdef3:2">.)</span></span>

### 

<span key="8d690ef793e04969aa21166a8c80b50b"><span offset-key="8d690ef793e04969aa21166a8c80b50b:0">Format</span></span>

<span key="fcb8a7cca27640bbbbea917893ed6c44"><span offset-key="fcb8a7cca27640bbbbea917893ed6c44:0">An OpenAPI document that conforms to the OpenAPI Specification is itself a JSON object, which may be represented either in JSON or YAML format.</span></span>

<span key="3987d518467d4d6aa9be86f412323c33"><span offset-key="3987d518467d4d6aa9be86f412323c33:0">For example, if a field has an array value, the JSON array representation will be used:</span></span>

1

<span key="f6bb7f074e4e464ba11fcc31e94effe5"><span offset-key="f6bb7f074e4e464ba11fcc31e94effe5:0">{ "field": \[ 1, 2, 3 \]}</span></span>

<img src="data:image/svg+xml;base64," class="r-h7gdob r-10ptun7 r-1vzi8xi" />

Copied!

<span key="1777795651684999bb4bbdecdff07ece"><span offset-key="1777795651684999bb4bbdecdff07ece:0">All field names in the specification are </span>**case sensitive**<span offset-key="1777795651684999bb4bbdecdff07ece:2">. This includes all fields that are used as keys in a map, except where explicitly noted that keys are </span>**case insensitive**<span offset-key="1777795651684999bb4bbdecdff07ece:4">.</span></span>

<span key="3251196ff47444d89a141073598b5eeb"><span offset-key="3251196ff47444d89a141073598b5eeb:0">The schema exposes two types of fields: Fixed fields, which have a declared name, and Patterned fields, which declare a regex pattern for the field name.</span></span>

<span key="8d81bb2381734c15956b381398db737f"><span offset-key="8d81bb2381734c15956b381398db737f:0">Patterned fields MUST have unique names within the containing object.</span></span>

<span key="fb30627c30b24a109effd50758a931c8"><span offset-key="fb30627c30b24a109effd50758a931c8:0">In order to preserve the ability to round-trip between YAML and JSON formats, YAML version </span></span><a href="https://yaml.org/spec/1.2/spec.html" class="css-4rbku5 css-1dbjc4n r-1loqt21 r-1471scf r-1otgn73 r-1i6wzkk r-lrvibr"><span data-key="f41105d7eee5484ea3ea027c3ea0f48e" data-rnw-int-class="nearest_257-34236_259-34237-237__"><span data-key="a2a373bad21e4ad987fb0a1ad8ced3a8"><span data-offset-key="a2a373bad21e4ad987fb0a1ad8ced3a8:0">1.2</span></span></span></a><span key="20b6619148264ac59a04b850e1a30be7"><span offset-key="20b6619148264ac59a04b850e1a30be7:0"> is RECOMMENDED along with some additional constraints:</span></span>

-   <img src="data:image/svg+xml;base64," class="r-1nf4jbm r-1vzi8xi" />

    <span key="fb8e3574069c4ce08bfe647f7b2b8c84"><span offset-key="fb8e3574069c4ce08bfe647f7b2b8c84:0">Tags MUST be limited to those allowed by the </span></span><a href="https://yaml.org/spec/1.2/spec.html#id2803231" class="css-4rbku5 css-1dbjc4n r-1loqt21 r-1471scf r-1otgn73 r-1i6wzkk r-lrvibr"><span data-key="975e728312e84f769cda250df9fc472d" data-rnw-int-class="nearest_257-34236_259-34237-237__"><span data-key="8456f921207444fa863abf44b2467660"><span data-offset-key="8456f921207444fa863abf44b2467660:0">JSON Schema ruleset</span></span></span></a><span key="090f7f14a5cf441ab90b6d209ac6a0c3"><span offset-key="090f7f14a5cf441ab90b6d209ac6a0c3:0">.</span></span>

    <span key="5f13d29983d74cf1baeffd0e1189a32c"><span offset-key="5f13d29983d74cf1baeffd0e1189a32c:0">Keys used in YAML maps MUST be limited to a scalar string, as defined by the </span></span><a href="https://yaml.org/spec/1.2/spec.html#id2802346" class="css-4rbku5 css-1dbjc4n r-1loqt21 r-1471scf r-1otgn73 r-1i6wzkk r-lrvibr"><span data-key="37f8b728b3dd4edb9da66e89a6a47898" data-rnw-int-class="nearest_257-34236_259-34237-237__"><span data-key="6b809d68306145d7ac01aeeb57061dae"><span data-offset-key="6b809d68306145d7ac01aeeb57061dae:0">YAML Failsafe schema ruleset</span></span></span></a><span key="b2b2dfde0ce841cc834c5c57a19f7d05"><span offset-key="b2b2dfde0ce841cc834c5c57a19f7d05:0">.</span></span>

<span key="d8c8444731294926806281c6829a4765">**Note:**<span offset-key="d8c8444731294926806281c6829a4765:1"> While APIs may be defined by OpenAPI documents in either YAML or JSON format, the API request and response bodies and other content are not required to be JSON or YAML.</span></span>

### 

<span key="0e8c6603713c429ab3006e992999371b"><span offset-key="0e8c6603713c429ab3006e992999371b:0">Document Structure</span></span>

<span key="8dd0a0459b2e4e818aabdd45a8a6526d"><span offset-key="8dd0a0459b2e4e818aabdd45a8a6526d:0">An OpenAPI document MAY be made up of a single document or be divided into multiple, connected parts at the discretion of the user. In the latter case, </span>`$ref`<span offset-key="8dd0a0459b2e4e818aabdd45a8a6526d:2"> fields MUST be used in the specification to reference those parts as follows from the </span></span><a href="https://json-schema.org" class="css-4rbku5 css-1dbjc4n r-1loqt21 r-1471scf r-1otgn73 r-1i6wzkk r-lrvibr"><span data-key="fa6a81f1994341fdbb0d81fafdff3696" data-rnw-int-class="nearest_257-34236_259-34237-237__"><span data-key="c246ae550ff9415eacece2aa681ac3b0"><span data-offset-key="c246ae550ff9415eacece2aa681ac3b0:0">JSON Schema</span></span></span></a><span key="b02d56c0db3a4f768b58ba93ebda6f7e"><span offset-key="b02d56c0db3a4f768b58ba93ebda6f7e:0"> definitions.</span></span>

<span key="d638295e4a6640de99a74c30695329b2"><span offset-key="d638295e4a6640de99a74c30695329b2:0">It is RECOMMENDED that the root OpenAPI document be named: </span>`openapi.json`<span offset-key="d638295e4a6640de99a74c30695329b2:2"> or </span>`openapi.yaml`<span offset-key="d638295e4a6640de99a74c30695329b2:4">.</span></span>

### 

<span key="c92705be058443c8abd2720a2f24f96c"><span offset-key="c92705be058443c8abd2720a2f24f96c:0">Data Types</span></span>

<span key="268942f2b51a462ba0957f3c1ea617bc"><span offset-key="268942f2b51a462ba0957f3c1ea617bc:0">Primitive data types in the OAS are based on the types supported by the </span></span><a href="https://tools.ietf.org/html/draft-wright-json-schema-00#section-4.2" class="css-4rbku5 css-1dbjc4n r-1loqt21 r-1471scf r-1otgn73 r-1i6wzkk r-lrvibr"><span data-key="bb16df250dd04b55ba9a49533710ce14" data-rnw-int-class="nearest_257-34236_259-34237-237__"><span data-key="1df095800a15498d9d4c22d06c18387d"><span data-offset-key="1df095800a15498d9d4c22d06c18387d:0">JSON Schema Specification Wright Draft 00</span></span></span></a><span key="1c470bf69d1949f891c832ebf5f530f2"><span offset-key="1c470bf69d1949f891c832ebf5f530f2:0">. Note that </span>`integer`<span offset-key="1c470bf69d1949f891c832ebf5f530f2:2"> as a type is also supported and is defined as a JSON number without a fraction or exponent part. </span>`null`<span offset-key="1c470bf69d1949f891c832ebf5f530f2:4"> is not supported as a type (see </span></span><a href="https://swagger.io/specification/#schema-nullable" class="css-4rbku5 css-1dbjc4n r-1loqt21 r-1471scf r-1otgn73 r-1i6wzkk r-lrvibr"><span data-key="cc00fdde34834962acf8e68c1cd1a6e2" data-rnw-int-class="nearest_257-34236_259-34237-237__"><span data-key="e1bc29a203ee451aa6d58c540b7d0ecb"><code class="r-1vckr1u r-z2wwpe r-uibjmv r-m2pi6t r-1hvjb8t" data-slate-leaf="true" data-offset-key="e1bc29a203ee451aa6d58c540b7d0ecb:0">nullable</code></span></span></a><span key="d351024163d54038b1859e6511c16c98"><span offset-key="d351024163d54038b1859e6511c16c98:0"> for an alternative solution). Models are defined using the </span></span><a href="https://swagger.io/specification/#schema-object" class="css-4rbku5 css-1dbjc4n r-1loqt21 r-1471scf r-1otgn73 r-1i6wzkk r-lrvibr"><span data-key="d745eb0aa9374d74bf095b2f172b074a" data-rnw-int-class="nearest_257-34236_259-34237-237__"><span data-key="c26399c5eb0a40d8a83a54a6c419a46a"><span data-offset-key="c26399c5eb0a40d8a83a54a6c419a46a:0">Schema Object</span></span></span></a><span key="5e803247ed1244fca2aea744e634431b"><span offset-key="5e803247ed1244fca2aea744e634431b:0">, which is an extended subset of JSON Schema Specification Wright Draft 00.</span></span>

<span key="ffaf552c38734d10a165ad6683c63845"><span offset-key="ffaf552c38734d10a165ad6683c63845:0">Primitives have an optional modifier property: </span>`format`<span offset-key="ffaf552c38734d10a165ad6683c63845:2">. OAS uses several known formats to define in fine detail the data type being used. However, to support documentation needs, the </span>`format`<span offset-key="ffaf552c38734d10a165ad6683c63845:4"> property is an open </span>`string`<span offset-key="ffaf552c38734d10a165ad6683c63845:6">-valued property, and can have any value. Formats such as </span>`"email"`<span offset-key="ffaf552c38734d10a165ad6683c63845:8">, </span>`"uuid"`<span offset-key="ffaf552c38734d10a165ad6683c63845:10">, and so on, MAY be used even though undefined by this specification. Types that are not accompanied by a </span>`format`<span offset-key="ffaf552c38734d10a165ad6683c63845:12"> property follow the type definition in the JSON Schema. Tools that do not recognize a specific </span>`format`<span offset-key="ffaf552c38734d10a165ad6683c63845:14"> MAY default back to the </span>`type`<span offset-key="ffaf552c38734d10a165ad6683c63845:16"> alone, as if the </span>`format`<span offset-key="ffaf552c38734d10a165ad6683c63845:18"> is not specified.</span></span>

<span key="79fcf26a3e0044e2aaeb0340b7a6b3a8"><span offset-key="79fcf26a3e0044e2aaeb0340b7a6b3a8:0">The formats defined by the OAS are:</span></span>

<span key="35dec1f8ccb246b5afdf14059c0897a3"><span offset-key="35dec1f8ccb246b5afdf14059c0897a3:0">Relative References in URLs</span></span>

<span key="8ad744c557e54140a54d0c202b6a48e3"><span offset-key="8ad744c557e54140a54d0c202b6a48e3:0">Unless specified otherwise, all properties that are URLs MAY be relative references as defined by </span></span><a href="https://tools.ietf.org/html/rfc3986#section-4.2" class="css-4rbku5 css-1dbjc4n r-1loqt21 r-1471scf r-1otgn73 r-1i6wzkk r-lrvibr"><span data-key="1bd72e05ba424cf294e20dd6edb1f9fe" data-rnw-int-class="nearest_257-34236_259-34237-237__"><span data-key="edea5357ecf74b61b4e6363f6b061cb8"><span data-offset-key="edea5357ecf74b61b4e6363f6b061cb8:0">RFC3986</span></span></span></a><span key="9fdb11c552554511869cd765cdd98ac7"><span offset-key="9fdb11c552554511869cd765cdd98ac7:0">. Relative references are resolved using the URLs defined in the </span></span><a href="https://swagger.io/specification/#server-object" class="css-4rbku5 css-1dbjc4n r-1loqt21 r-1471scf r-1otgn73 r-1i6wzkk r-lrvibr"><span data-key="29f626307957477c9f27f43769e9ca99" data-rnw-int-class="nearest_257-34236_259-34237-237__"><span data-key="1e08d7000fb741719d47d93f0d869b1f"><code class="r-1vckr1u r-z2wwpe r-uibjmv r-m2pi6t r-1hvjb8t" data-slate-leaf="true" data-offset-key="1e08d7000fb741719d47d93f0d869b1f:0">Server Object</code></span></span></a><span key="7c69bd8e0fa34a85a9eb3562e4db3546"><span offset-key="7c69bd8e0fa34a85a9eb3562e4db3546:0"> as a Base URI.</span></span>

<span key="f859940d08d9402192fab6c5802c442c"><span offset-key="f859940d08d9402192fab6c5802c442c:0">Relative references used in </span>`$ref`<span offset-key="f859940d08d9402192fab6c5802c442c:2"> are processed as per </span></span><a href="https://tools.ietf.org/html/draft-pbryan-zyp-json-ref-03" class="css-4rbku5 css-1dbjc4n r-1loqt21 r-1471scf r-1otgn73 r-1i6wzkk r-lrvibr"><span data-key="1beb67acf04347418935ad0fb8d9bb5e" data-rnw-int-class="nearest_257-34236_259-34237-237__"><span data-key="7a9ce720fdfe4d12b0cd86890a42b53f"><span data-offset-key="7a9ce720fdfe4d12b0cd86890a42b53f:0">JSON Reference</span></span></span></a><span key="be73df224e3b481894e1cb24155983d2"><span offset-key="be73df224e3b481894e1cb24155983d2:0">, using the URL of the current document as the base URI. See also the </span></span><a href="https://swagger.io/specification/#reference-object" class="css-4rbku5 css-1dbjc4n r-1loqt21 r-1471scf r-1otgn73 r-1i6wzkk r-lrvibr"><span data-key="a45b6bcd01b947268b6a1d077eb23c60" data-rnw-int-class="nearest_257-34236_259-34237-237__"><span data-key="9bf1e9b9d8ae485eb8ec04eb69797ad8"><span data-offset-key="9bf1e9b9d8ae485eb8ec04eb69797ad8:0">Reference Object</span></span></span></a><span key="7eb3b74051d144129e0dde1792159dad"><span offset-key="7eb3b74051d144129e0dde1792159dad:0">.</span></span>

### 

<span key="ca7d6ea777f84ba9b869a8e7ec829038"><span offset-key="ca7d6ea777f84ba9b869a8e7ec829038:0">Schema</span></span>

<span key="bec69c2b77db49108e20f908ddeb4b02"><span offset-key="bec69c2b77db49108e20f908ddeb4b02:0">In the following description, if a field is not explicitly </span>**REQUIRED**<span offset-key="bec69c2b77db49108e20f908ddeb4b02:2"> or described with a MUST or SHALL, it can be considered OPTIONAL.</span></span>

<span key="aeca78c1bf084949997e325c28c6f9a2">**OpenAPI Object**</span>

<span key="7ba7be3beb4f4eebbc1af8fa72899efb"><span offset-key="7ba7be3beb4f4eebbc1af8fa72899efb:0">This is the root document object of the </span></span><a href="https://swagger.io/specification/#oas-document" class="css-4rbku5 css-1dbjc4n r-1loqt21 r-1471scf r-1otgn73 r-1i6wzkk r-lrvibr"><span data-key="d91c4e1bf00b415a90e8158085e67b72" data-rnw-int-class="nearest_257-34236_259-34237-237__"><span data-key="b5dd761b6ae14cbaaf24d5e3ad97756f"><span data-offset-key="b5dd761b6ae14cbaaf24d5e3ad97756f:0">OpenAPI document</span></span></span></a><span key="28b97d1e2b124ae1907e180cc8240faa"><span offset-key="28b97d1e2b124ae1907e180cc8240faa:0">.</span></span>

<span key="ea65a3eb5722473ca51958f2ea1e64bf"><span offset-key="ea65a3eb5722473ca51958f2ea1e64bf:0">Describes a single operation parameter.</span></span>

<span key="e0109f245bff4e909b02da265a43eeeb"><span offset-key="e0109f245bff4e909b02da265a43eeeb:0">A unique parameter is defined by a combination of a </span></span><a href="https://swagger.io/specification/#parameter-name" class="css-4rbku5 css-1dbjc4n r-1loqt21 r-1471scf r-1otgn73 r-1i6wzkk r-lrvibr"><span data-key="86ffa26aeff54bb5bafb1ddb051548a5" data-rnw-int-class="nearest_257-34236_259-34237-237__"><span data-key="fd7bc762927c4c76a71b6ff0b1189843"><span data-offset-key="fd7bc762927c4c76a71b6ff0b1189843:0">name</span></span></span></a><span key="7c0acd00cc5a483f89090a28434bb901"><span offset-key="7c0acd00cc5a483f89090a28434bb901:0"> and </span></span><a href="https://swagger.io/specification/#parameter-in" class="css-4rbku5 css-1dbjc4n r-1loqt21 r-1471scf r-1otgn73 r-1i6wzkk r-lrvibr"><span data-key="761794df729b4c3ea50b54390bc616aa" data-rnw-int-class="nearest_257-34236_259-34237-237__"><span data-key="47933bacf5094ba198e741b86a49f87e"><span data-offset-key="47933bacf5094ba198e741b86a49f87e:0">location</span></span></span></a><span key="3cb0fefb136d49b68cb16b1bb189ed7c"><span offset-key="3cb0fefb136d49b68cb16b1bb189ed7c:0">.</span></span>

<span key="971d043ba85a49459b40cfb0f1e2f9a0">**Parameter Locations**</span>

<span key="ba56c35c25d04b35b58e4c36d60b108c"><span offset-key="ba56c35c25d04b35b58e4c36d60b108c:0">There are four possible parameter locations specified by the </span>`in`<span offset-key="ba56c35c25d04b35b58e4c36d60b108c:2"> field:</span></span>

-   <img src="data:image/svg+xml;base64," class="r-1nf4jbm r-1vzi8xi" />

    <span key="d82001f4dd18447bbdd5189d83c3c34d"><span offset-key="d82001f4dd18447bbdd5189d83c3c34d:0">path - Used together with </span></span><a href="https://swagger.io/specification/#path-templating" class="css-4rbku5 css-1dbjc4n r-1loqt21 r-1471scf r-1otgn73 r-1i6wzkk r-lrvibr"><span data-key="be3cd6dbfe2d4ab88d663a4aa42bacf4" data-rnw-int-class="nearest_257-34236_259-34237-237__"><span data-key="4aab5bf014194e75a643978c1d92e063"><span data-offset-key="4aab5bf014194e75a643978c1d92e063:0">Path Templating</span></span></span></a><span key="93db4ff77f274cfb9b425c738ebc2369"><span offset-key="93db4ff77f274cfb9b425c738ebc2369:0">, where the parameter value is actually part of the operation's URL. This does not include the host or base path of the API. For example, in </span>`/items/{itemId}`<span offset-key="93db4ff77f274cfb9b425c738ebc2369:2">, the path parameter is </span>`itemId`<span offset-key="93db4ff77f274cfb9b425c738ebc2369:4">.</span></span>

-   <img src="data:image/svg+xml;base64," class="r-1nf4jbm r-1vzi8xi" />

    <span key="828b6534855c42618c022813b2732916"><span offset-key="828b6534855c42618c022813b2732916:0">query - Parameters that are appended to the URL. For example, in </span>`/items?id=###`<span offset-key="828b6534855c42618c022813b2732916:2">, the query parameter is </span>`id`<span offset-key="828b6534855c42618c022813b2732916:4">.</span></span>

-   <img src="data:image/svg+xml;base64," class="r-1nf4jbm r-1vzi8xi" />

    <span key="01ac3157748848c3a749d63e2fea7780"><span offset-key="01ac3157748848c3a749d63e2fea7780:0">header - Custom headers that are expected as part of the request. Note that </span></span><a href="https://tools.ietf.org/html/rfc7230#page-22" class="css-4rbku5 css-1dbjc4n r-1loqt21 r-1471scf r-1otgn73 r-1i6wzkk r-lrvibr"><span data-key="f4095dc8419c423a8b0b6826cd3591b4" data-rnw-int-class="nearest_257-34236_259-34237-237__"><span data-key="2333036f6c164c528038b74133738eb8"><span data-offset-key="2333036f6c164c528038b74133738eb8:0">RFC7230</span></span></span></a><span key="6d9dfee71be94857aa4094cdf31665cc"><span offset-key="6d9dfee71be94857aa4094cdf31665cc:0"> states header names are case insensitive.</span></span>

-   <img src="data:image/svg+xml;base64," class="r-1nf4jbm r-1vzi8xi" />

    <span key="b3562d80196c4abb8784049c26246aa2"><span offset-key="b3562d80196c4abb8784049c26246aa2:0">cookie - Used to pass a specific cookie value to the API.</span></span>

<span key="514781e2fb6449e59cea3a4ba088b626"><span offset-key="514781e2fb6449e59cea3a4ba088b626:0">When passing complex objects in the </span>`application/x-www-form-urlencoded`<span offset-key="514781e2fb6449e59cea3a4ba088b626:2"> content type, the default serialization strategy of such properties is described in the </span></span><a href="https://swagger.io/specification/#encoding-object" class="css-4rbku5 css-1dbjc4n r-1loqt21 r-1471scf r-1otgn73 r-1i6wzkk r-lrvibr"><span data-key="b1b8de42842946ea8df0e400fe7b0054" data-rnw-int-class="nearest_257-34236_259-34237-237__"><span data-key="db5a619ad63a4c1f8240be673943c195"><code class="r-1vckr1u r-z2wwpe r-uibjmv r-m2pi6t r-1hvjb8t" data-slate-leaf="true" data-offset-key="db5a619ad63a4c1f8240be673943c195:0">Encoding Object</code></span></span></a><span key="c4727d4ff6bf425191c7f8e6530b799b"><span offset-key="c4727d4ff6bf425191c7f8e6530b799b:0">'s </span></span><a href="https://swagger.io/specification/#encoding-style" class="css-4rbku5 css-1dbjc4n r-1loqt21 r-1471scf r-1otgn73 r-1i6wzkk r-lrvibr"><span data-key="a5ae4f760e414fb390f161ba43b4ae25" data-rnw-int-class="nearest_257-34236_259-34237-237__"><span data-key="08cc526332e042ecb250605e459fc6fb"><code class="r-1vckr1u r-z2wwpe r-uibjmv r-m2pi6t r-1hvjb8t" data-slate-leaf="true" data-offset-key="08cc526332e042ecb250605e459fc6fb:0">style</code></span></span></a><span key="7a2499efad2044dc86226aad8639d2cd"><span offset-key="7a2499efad2044dc86226aad8639d2cd:0"> property as </span>`form`<span offset-key="7a2499efad2044dc86226aad8639d2cd:2">.</span></span>

<span key="a98776679a244d81934abc875d70faba">**Special Considerations for multipart Content**</span>

<span key="abf0ad306d934431a7a58f25b87f12aa"><span offset-key="abf0ad306d934431a7a58f25b87f12aa:0">It is common to use </span>`multipart/form-data`<span offset-key="abf0ad306d934431a7a58f25b87f12aa:2"> as a </span>`Content-Type`<span offset-key="abf0ad306d934431a7a58f25b87f12aa:4"> when transferring request bodies to operations. In contrast to 2.0, a </span>`schema`<span offset-key="abf0ad306d934431a7a58f25b87f12aa:6"> is REQUIRED to define the input parameters to the operation when using </span>`multipart`<span offset-key="abf0ad306d934431a7a58f25b87f12aa:8"> content. This supports complex structures as well as supporting mechanisms for multiple file uploads.</span></span>

<span key="71013ca8355f469e93d96289aa83ef33"><span offset-key="71013ca8355f469e93d96289aa83ef33:0">When passing in </span>`multipart`<span offset-key="71013ca8355f469e93d96289aa83ef33:2"> types, boundaries MAY be used to separate sections of the content being transferred â€” thus, the following default </span>`Content-Type`<span offset-key="71013ca8355f469e93d96289aa83ef33:4">s are defined for </span>`multipart`<span offset-key="71013ca8355f469e93d96289aa83ef33:6">:</span></span>

-   <img src="data:image/svg+xml;base64," class="r-1nf4jbm r-1vzi8xi" />

    <span key="7ccf39839687465fbf8425ffaac81f4d"><span offset-key="7ccf39839687465fbf8425ffaac81f4d:0">If the property is a primitive, or an array of primitive values, the default Content-Type is </span>`text/plain`</span>

-   <img src="data:image/svg+xml;base64," class="r-1nf4jbm r-1vzi8xi" />

    <span key="0535772e8caf48cd927c65e0a1a7f703"><span offset-key="0535772e8caf48cd927c65e0a1a7f703:0">If the property is complex, or an array of complex values, the default Content-Type is </span>`application/json`</span>

-   <img src="data:image/svg+xml;base64," class="r-1nf4jbm r-1vzi8xi" />

    <span key="bbfc405d0a4340bfbd7ec8ebb6cc9cfe"><span offset-key="bbfc405d0a4340bfbd7ec8ebb6cc9cfe:0">If the property is a </span>`type: string`<span offset-key="bbfc405d0a4340bfbd7ec8ebb6cc9cfe:2"> with </span>`format: binary`<span offset-key="bbfc405d0a4340bfbd7ec8ebb6cc9cfe:4"> or </span>`format: base64`<span offset-key="bbfc405d0a4340bfbd7ec8ebb6cc9cfe:6"> (aka a file object), the default Content-Type is </span>`application/octet-stream`</span>

<span key="b74eec8325154fb8939c7244a10dac58"><span offset-key="b74eec8325154fb8939c7244a10dac58:0">Examples:</span></span>

1

<span key="12cf8fcb52e24825be002bd91974bb44"><span offset-key="12cf8fcb52e24825be002bd91974bb44:0">requestBody: content: multipart/form-data: schema: type: object properties: id: type: string format: uuid address: # default Content-Type for objects is \`application/json\` type: object properties: {} profileImage: # default Content-Type for string/binary is \`application/octet-stream\` type: string format: binary children: # default Content-Type for arrays is based on the \`inner\` type (text/plain here) type: array items: type: string addresses: # default Content-Type for arrays is based on the \`inner\` type (object shown, so \`application/json\` in this example) type: array items: type: '#/components/schemas/Address'</span></span>

<span key="0fd920fe3a0844a19caeff925ca0ae3c"><span offset-key="0fd920fe3a0844a19caeff925ca0ae3c:0">An </span>`encoding`<span offset-key="0fd920fe3a0844a19caeff925ca0ae3c:2"> attribute is introduced to give you control over the serialization of parts of </span>`multipart`<span offset-key="0fd920fe3a0844a19caeff925ca0ae3c:4"> request bodies. This attribute is </span>*only*<span offset-key="0fd920fe3a0844a19caeff925ca0ae3c:6"> applicable to </span>`multipart`<span offset-key="0fd920fe3a0844a19caeff925ca0ae3c:8"> and </span>`application/x-www-form-urlencoded`<span offset-key="0fd920fe3a0844a19caeff925ca0ae3c:10"> request bodies.</span></span>

<span key="cbe1d68256f94fe3aa6c259f1a46ab66">**Callback Object**</span>

<span key="f5a48076dd5d4725aed8674f0e37448e"><span offset-key="f5a48076dd5d4725aed8674f0e37448e:0">A map of possible out-of band callbacks related to the parent operation. Each value in the map is a </span></span><a href="https://swagger.io/specification/#path-item-object" class="css-4rbku5 css-1dbjc4n r-1loqt21 r-1471scf r-1otgn73 r-1i6wzkk r-lrvibr"><span data-key="b117ee10f1f54aac9dee24a40cfb9f37" data-rnw-int-class="nearest_257-34236_259-34237-237__"><span data-key="a29e93fb456f457bafbb9c02bb488b58"><span data-offset-key="a29e93fb456f457bafbb9c02bb488b58:0">Path Item Object</span></span></span></a><span key="cc5c2ae3a52d445680786751126408f5"><span offset-key="cc5c2ae3a52d445680786751126408f5:0"> that describes a set of requests that may be initiated by the API provider and the expected responses. The key value used to identify the path item object is an expression, evaluated at runtime, that identifies a URL to use for the callback operation.</span></span>

<span key="f010b4245de54caca2a86e1262a65e38">**Link Object**</span>

<span key="37f3c223975c44919adae47418b50f92"><span offset-key="37f3c223975c44919adae47418b50f92:0">The </span>`Link object`<span offset-key="37f3c223975c44919adae47418b50f92:2"> represents a possible design-time link for a response. The presence of a link does not guarantee the caller's ability to successfully invoke it, rather it provides a known relationship and traversal mechanism between responses and other operations.</span></span>

<span key="b246167de82c40dc85115a07d3764b63"><span offset-key="b246167de82c40dc85115a07d3764b63:0">Unlike </span>*dynamic*<span offset-key="b246167de82c40dc85115a07d3764b63:2"> links (i.e. links provided </span>**in**<span offset-key="b246167de82c40dc85115a07d3764b63:4"> the response payload), the OAS linking mechanism does not require link information in the runtime response.</span></span>

<span key="a8a52062b02e4b3889021bcebf675527"><span offset-key="a8a52062b02e4b3889021bcebf675527:0">For computing links, and providing instructions to execute them, a </span></span><a href="https://swagger.io/specification/#runtime-expression" class="css-4rbku5 css-1dbjc4n r-1loqt21 r-1471scf r-1otgn73 r-1i6wzkk r-lrvibr"><span data-key="1096966aa5644767baf9a79abae55060" data-rnw-int-class="nearest_257-34236_259-34237-237__"><span data-key="3841dd31565f4383be42fbfb997952a1"><span data-offset-key="3841dd31565f4383be42fbfb997952a1:0">runtime expression</span></span></span></a><span key="052d057ba5104dfcb02d5cf8e786bf0b"><span offset-key="052d057ba5104dfcb02d5cf8e786bf0b:0"> is used for accessing values in an operation and using them as parameters while invoking the linked operation.</span></span>

<span key="75a4f19ba431422ab80f759442c91125">**Runtime Expressions**</span>

<span key="09f8a7e606074cc1a2bb78ad512f5d36"><span offset-key="09f8a7e606074cc1a2bb78ad512f5d36:0">Runtime expressions allow defining values based on information that will only be available within the HTTP message in an actual API call. This mechanism is used by </span></span><a href="https://swagger.io/specification/#link-object" class="css-4rbku5 css-1dbjc4n r-1loqt21 r-1471scf r-1otgn73 r-1i6wzkk r-lrvibr"><span data-key="86a78960b78f4694b1f5a1d817935505" data-rnw-int-class="nearest_257-34236_259-34237-237__"><span data-key="ac950c0fed44441eb91a121020228c08"><span data-offset-key="ac950c0fed44441eb91a121020228c08:0">Link Objects</span></span></span></a><span key="1edde2456ad644759966122f5da288a3"><span offset-key="1edde2456ad644759966122f5da288a3:0"> and </span></span><a href="https://swagger.io/specification/#callback-object" class="css-4rbku5 css-1dbjc4n r-1loqt21 r-1471scf r-1otgn73 r-1i6wzkk r-lrvibr"><span data-key="e366c734e6a34a7e9d68f71d5be664cd" data-rnw-int-class="nearest_257-34236_259-34237-237__"><span data-key="471e9cf46ac049abba4061cb3caa70cd"><span data-offset-key="471e9cf46ac049abba4061cb3caa70cd:0">Callback Objects</span></span></span></a><span key="2c7a9a45084844e1a2e5886a517f0070"><span offset-key="2c7a9a45084844e1a2e5886a517f0070:0">.</span></span>

<span key="6a877e6d11504ac4a2ee237b680bb687"><span offset-key="6a877e6d11504ac4a2ee237b680bb687:0">The runtime expression is defined by the following </span></span><a href="https://tools.ietf.org/html/rfc5234" class="css-4rbku5 css-1dbjc4n r-1loqt21 r-1471scf r-1otgn73 r-1i6wzkk r-lrvibr"><span data-key="c5b19bf140604b9eaba5a4216295775b" data-rnw-int-class="nearest_257-34236_259-34237-237__"><span data-key="6c7e6cb55cf84d17b0df8e4ee22eb332"><span data-offset-key="6c7e6cb55cf84d17b0df8e4ee22eb332:0">ABNF</span></span></span></a><span key="30e8aed209f84e5bbe9aeaeb13650d4b"><span offset-key="30e8aed209f84e5bbe9aeaeb13650d4b:0"> syntax</span></span>

1

<span key="a17268dcc0d84fe1b40e1fe5dd4af7c8"><span offset-key="a17268dcc0d84fe1b40e1fe5dd4af7c8:0"><span slate-zero-width="z">â€‹</span></span></span><a href="https://swagger.io/specification/#discriminator-object" class="css-4rbku5 css-1dbjc4n r-1loqt21 r-1471scf r-1otgn73 r-1i6wzkk r-lrvibr"><span data-key="6ceaa445c87d43e2951e7b85ad26a0ad" data-rnw-int-class="nearest_257-34236_259-34237-237__"><span data-key="a692de74b3484c6896b4f1691e750f79"><span data-offset-key="a692de74b3484c6896b4f1691e750f79:0">Discriminator Object</span></span></span></a><span key="f27736c1a0b34567ac26b670e8bd2f73"><span offset-key="f27736c1a0b34567ac26b670e8bd2f73:0"><span slate-zero-width="z">â€‹</span></span></span>

<span key="fdfed165f1974a5cb4d075af964ff8d2"><span offset-key="fdfed165f1974a5cb4d075af964ff8d2:0">Adds support for polymorphism. <span key="9ff4f897fd804e63a106ceca5a77dd42"><span offset-key="9ff4f897fd804e63a106ceca5a77dd42:0">readOnly</span></span>

<span key="1e489f4296b142aeb444046f54ac70fb">`boolean`</span>

<span key="00c6ad09f27849398b77756689235efd"><span offset-key="00c6ad09f27849398b77756689235efd:0">Relevant only for Schema </span>`"properties"`<span offset-key="00c6ad09f27849398b77756689235efd:2"> definitions. If the property is marked as </span>`readOnly`<span offset-key="00c6ad09f27849398b77756689235efd:4"> being </span>`true`<span offset-key="00c6ad09f27849398b77756689235efd:6"> and is in the </span>`required`<span offset-key="00c6ad09f27849398b77756689235efd:8"> list, the </span>`required`<span offset-key="00c6ad09f27849398b77756689235efd:10"> will take effect on the response only. Default value is </span>`false`<span offset-key="00c6ad09f27849398b77756689235efd:18">.</span></span>

<span key="be487e7240d44d4bb4cbf45fa85823a1"><span offset-key="be487e7240d44d4bb4cbf45fa85823a1:0">This object MAY be extended with </span></span><a href="https://swagger.io/specification/#specification-extensions" class="css-4rbku5 css-1dbjc4n r-1loqt21 r-1471scf r-1otgn73 r-1i6wzkk r-lrvibr"><span data-key="99ab8597bd8944e796fe680ad824a7bc" data-rnw-int-class="nearest_257-34236_259-34237-237__"><span data-key="bebb87bd009c49bf8db6e71d524a3339"><span data-offset-key="bebb87bd009c49bf8db6e71d524a3339:0">Specification Extensions</span></span></span></a><span key="9fe0a2f8ff714d8cb51a2719d7777f22"><span offset-key="9fe0a2f8ff714d8cb51a2719d7777f22:0">.</span></span>

<span key="2d4c53e03d7c4f45935161b39a83edb7">**Composition and Inheritance (Polymorphism)**</span>

<span key="857741bff5694d42a2d5fd1871241f0f"><span offset-key="857741bff5694d42a2d5fd1871241f0f:0">The OpenAPI Specification allows combining and extending model definitions using the </span>`allOf`<span offset-key="857741bff5694d42a2d5fd1871241f0f:2"> property of JSON Schema, in effect offering model composition. </span>`allOf`<span offset-key="857741bff5694d42a2d5fd1871241f0f:4"> takes an array of object definitions that are validated </span>*independently*<span offset-key="857741bff5694d42a2d5fd1871241f0f:6"> but together compose a single object.</span></span>

<span key="bbbd5cd5f25740028c38b5e2e06544af"><span offset-key="bbbd5cd5f25740028c38b5e2e06544af:0">While composition offers model extensibility, it does not imply a hierarchy between the models. To support polymorphism, the OpenAPI Specification adds the </span>`discriminator`<span offset-key="bbbd5cd5f25740028c38b5e2e06544af:2"> field. When used, the </span>`discriminator`<span offset-key="bbbd5cd5f25740028c38b5e2e06544af:4"> will be the name of the property that decides which schema definition validates the structure of the model. As such, the </span>`discriminator`<span offset-key="bbbd5cd5f25740028c38b5e2e06544af:6"> field MUST be a required field. There are two ways to define the value of a discriminator for an inheriting instance.</span></span>

-   <img src="data:image/svg+xml;base64," class="r-1nf4jbm r-1vzi8xi" />

    <span key="55d0c90ea037453c8cec7291b2f8999b"><span offset-key="55d0c90ea037453c8cec7291b2f8999b:0">Use the schema name.</span></span>

-   <img src="data:image/svg+xml;base64," class="r-1nf4jbm r-1vzi8xi" />

    <span key="50b00c5c06ab4dcaaaa9146df52d85c7"><span offset-key="50b00c5c06ab4dcaaaa9146df52d85c7:0">Override the schema name by overriding the property with a new value. If a new value exists, this takes precedence over the schema name. As such, inline schema definitions, which do not have a given id, </span>*cannot*<span offset-key="50b00c5c06ab4dcaaaa9146df52d85c7:2"> be used in polymorphism.</span></span>

<span key="37961dfb724f4a1c95ab6b0190412cdd">**XML Modeling**</span>

<span key="8a2f28d1142a475599746681db2f0a39"><span offset-key="8a2f28d1142a475599746681db2f0a39:0">The </span></span><a href="https://swagger.io/specification/#schema-xml" class="css-4rbku5 css-1dbjc4n r-1loqt21 r-1471scf r-1otgn73 r-1i6wzkk r-lrvibr"><span data-key="c3242540056e4a14be995ac707a0e2b8" data-rnw-int-class="nearest_257-34236_259-34237-237__"><span data-key="420f1e896baf4faab9c8c7fb57ff424c"><span data-offset-key="420f1e896baf4faab9c8c7fb57ff424c:0">xml</span></span></span></a><span key="15d617156c864c27aae24319257e3620"><span offset-key="15d617156c864c27aae24319257e3620:0"> property allows extra definitions when translating the JSON definition to XML. The </span></span><a href="https://swagger.io/specification/#xml-object" class="css-4rbku5 css-1dbjc4n r-1loqt21 r-1471scf r-1otgn73 r-1i6wzkk r-lrvibr"><span data-key="13d85ea5abc645ecb6a8652d65f162c6" data-rnw-int-class="nearest_257-34236_259-34237-237__"><span data-key="21c55ad8fc6c4bda932ca3d45eea965d"><span data-offset-key="21c55ad8fc6c4bda932ca3d45eea965d:0">XML Object</span></span></span></a><span key="35143fb64c9148b98ff4f420b21af3a2"><span offset-key="35143fb64c9148b98ff4f420b21af3a2:0"> contains additional information about the available options.</span></span>

<span key="df4196a26bec4caeb17678a9d974ecce">**Discriminator Object**</span>

<span key="de5ae50df9d144c58a5386626f6d39e3"><span offset-key="de5ae50df9d144c58a5386626f6d39e3:0">When request bodies or response payloads may be one of a number of different schemas, a </span>`discriminator`<span offset-key="de5ae50df9d144c58a5386626f6d39e3:2"> object can be used to aid in serialization, deserialization, and validation. The discriminator is a specific object in a schema which is used to inform the consumer of the specification of an alternative schema based on the value associated with it.</span></span>

<span key="19c762cf0cfd41b2bebaf32effe58a8a"><span offset-key="19c762cf0cfd41b2bebaf32effe58a8a:0">When using the discriminator, </span>*inline*<span offset-key="19c762cf0cfd41b2bebaf32effe58a8a:2"> schemas will not be considered.</span></span>

<span key="dc212c4a5f8f400580fd0e27eb07ff29"><span offset-key="dc212c4a5f8f400580fd0e27eb07ff29:0">propertyName</span></span>

<span key="a9ea57e0aed84a4f834442884b128f84">`string`</span>

<span key="77837f5fc353461186a15c6749d58a45">**REQUIRED**<span offset-key="77837f5fc353461186a15c6749d58a45:1">. The name of the property in the payload that will hold the discriminator value.</span></span>

<span key="b5702af7b0eb4c5dac7591efe5aaef23"><span offset-key="b5702af7b0eb4c5dac7591efe5aaef23:0">mapping</span></span>

<span key="68f2332da5264bb2a73fdf7305fea4e3"><span offset-key="68f2332da5264bb2a73fdf7305fea4e3:0">Map\[</span>`string`<span offset-key="68f2332da5264bb2a73fdf7305fea4e3:2">, </span>`string`<span offset-key="68f2332da5264bb2a73fdf7305fea4e3:4">\]</span></span>

<span key="e52a2e1dd4144d1a80469630adf1b02f"><span offset-key="e52a2e1dd4144d1a80469630adf1b02f:0">An object to hold mappings between payload values and schema names or references.</span></span>

<span key="410cc48754124c42a739d2024c6ef03e"><span offset-key="410cc48754124c42a739d2024c6ef03e:0">The discriminator object is legal only when using one of the composite keywords </span>`oneOf`<span offset-key="410cc48754124c42a739d2024c6ef03e:2">, </span>`anyOf`<span offset-key="410cc48754124c42a739d2024c6ef03e:4">, </span>`allOf`<span offset-key="410cc48754124c42a739d2024c6ef03e:6">.</span></span>

<span key="78507f44a2d64004ab51dd66a83c004b"><span offset-key="78507f44a2d64004ab51dd66a83c004b:0">In OAS 3.0, a response payload MAY be described to be exactly one of any number of types:</span></span>

1

<span key="c3b31ac2217f4fdc8abd9430159c0a9e"><span offset-key="c3b31ac2217f4fdc8abd9430159c0a9e:0">MyResponseType: oneOf: - $ref: '#/components/schemas/Cat' - $ref: '#/components/schemas/Dog' - $ref: '#/components/schemas/Lizard'</span></span>

<img src="data:image/svg+xml;base64," class="r-h7gdob r-10ptun7 r-1vzi8xi" />

Copied!

<span key="f4db0c4518184ddb9c88bf29ea4ae8c1"><span offset-key="f4db0c4518184ddb9c88bf29ea4ae8c1:0">which means the payload </span>*MUST*<span offset-key="f4db0c4518184ddb9c88bf29ea4ae8c1:2">, by validation, match exactly one of the schemas described by </span>`Cat`<span offset-key="f4db0c4518184ddb9c88bf29ea4ae8c1:4">, </span>`Dog`<span offset-key="f4db0c4518184ddb9c88bf29ea4ae8c1:6">, or </span>`Lizard`<span offset-key="f4db0c4518184ddb9c88bf29ea4ae8c1:8">. In this case, a discriminator MAY act as a "hint" to shortcut validation and selection of the matching schema which may be a costly operation, depending on the complexity of the schema. We can then describe exactly which field tells us which schema to use:</span></span>

1

<span key="85128aafa83a4f4ea26ebde9d6df82bb"><span offset-key="85128aafa83a4f4ea26ebde9d6df82bb:0">MyResponseType: oneOf: - $ref: '#/components/schemas/Cat' - $ref: '#/components/schemas/Dog' - $ref: '#/components/schemas/Lizard' discriminator: propertyName: petType</span></span>

<img src="data:image/svg+xml;base64," class="r-h7gdob r-10ptun7 r-1vzi8xi" />

Copied!

<span key="903d540799a14fc694e35b5f54a79406"><span offset-key="903d540799a14fc694e35b5f54a79406:0">The expectation now is that a property with name </span>`petType`<span offset-key="903d540799a14fc694e35b5f54a79406:2"> </span>*MUST*<span offset-key="903d540799a14fc694e35b5f54a79406:4"> be present in the response payload, and the value will correspond to the name of a schema defined in the OAS document. Thus the response payload:</span></span>

1

<span key="e0effc551dcb4fbc90df4cf5fa511152"><span offset-key="e0effc551dcb4fbc90df4cf5fa511152:0">{ "id": 12345, "petType": "Cat"}</span></span>

<img src="data:image/svg+xml;base64," class="r-h7gdob r-10ptun7 r-1vzi8xi" />

Copied!

<span key="c188c8b245a84493a05193a1418425d9"><span offset-key="c188c8b245a84493a05193a1418425d9:0">Will indicate that the </span>`Cat`<span offset-key="c188c8b245a84493a05193a1418425d9:2"> schema be used in conjunction with this payload.</span></span>

<span key="fec6999f3c4149dc8820710c9a850c57"><span offset-key="fec6999f3c4149dc8820710c9a850c57:0">In scenarios where the value of the discriminator field does not match the schema name or implicit mapping is not possible, an optional </span>`mapping`<span offset-key="fec6999f3c4149dc8820710c9a850c57:2"> definition MAY be used:</span></span>

1

<span key="e1e3aa2f292e4291a5ca31fa3d938b9a"><span offset-key="e1e3aa2f292e4291a5ca31fa3d938b9a:0">MyResponseType: oneOf: - $ref: '#/components/schemas/Cat' - $ref: '#/components/schemas/Dog' - $ref: '#/components/schemas/Lizard' - $ref: 'https://gigantic-server.com/schemas/Monster/schema.json' discriminator: propertyName: petType mapping: dog: '#/components/schemas/Dog' monster: 'https://gigantic-server.com/schemas/Monster/schema.json'</span></span>

<img src="data:image/svg+xml;base64," class="r-h7gdob r-10ptun7 r-1vzi8xi" />

Copied!

<span key="ed6cec6882b8402fb94fb09b57df2cfd"><span offset-key="ed6cec6882b8402fb94fb09b57df2cfd:0">Here the discriminator </span>*value*<span offset-key="ed6cec6882b8402fb94fb09b57df2cfd:2"> of </span>`dog`<span offset-key="ed6cec6882b8402fb94fb09b57df2cfd:4"> will map to the schema </span>`#/components/schemas/Dog`<span offset-key="ed6cec6882b8402fb94fb09b57df2cfd:6">, rather than the default (implicit) value of </span>`Dog`<span offset-key="ed6cec6882b8402fb94fb09b57df2cfd:8">. If the discriminator </span>*value*<span offset-key="ed6cec6882b8402fb94fb09b57df2cfd:10"> does not match an implicit or explicit mapping, no schema can be determined and validation SHOULD fail. Mapping keys MUST be string values, but tooling MAY convert response values to strings for comparison.</span></span>

<span key="e735a97b17844bfca60c250ccc7a5ac8"><span offset-key="e735a97b17844bfca60c250ccc7a5ac8:0">When used in conjunction with the </span>`anyOf`<span offset-key="e735a97b17844bfca60c250ccc7a5ac8:2"> construct, the use of the discriminator can avoid ambiguity where multiple schemas may satisfy a single payload.</span></span>

<span key="ce22eb24c6ec4c8f9cc68983a3897a4b"><span offset-key="ce22eb24c6ec4c8f9cc68983a3897a4b:0">In both the </span>`oneOf`<span offset-key="ce22eb24c6ec4c8f9cc68983a3897a4b:2"> and </span>`anyOf`<span offset-key="ce22eb24c6ec4c8f9cc68983a3897a4b:4"> use cases, all possible schemas MUST be listed explicitly. To avoid redundancy, the discriminator MAY be added to a parent schema definition, and all schemas comprising the parent schema in an </span>`allOf`<span offset-key="ce22eb24c6ec4c8f9cc68983a3897a4b:6"> construct may be used as an alternate schema.</span></span>

<span key="588aacf3b85d41fd82bb3f54e70d31df"><span offset-key="588aacf3b85d41fd82bb3f54e70d31df:0">For example:</span></span>

<span key="b60eda3459354ed09363590a8b2f4569"><span offset-key="b60eda3459354ed09363590a8b2f4569:0">components: schemas: Pet: type: object required: - petType properties: petType: type: string discriminator: propertyName: petType mapping: dog: Dog Cat: allOf: - $ref: '#/components/schemas/Pet' - type: object # all other properties specific to a \`Cat\` properties: name: type: string Dog: allOf: - $ref: '#/components/schemas/Pet' - type: object # all other properties specific to a \`Dog\` properties: bark: type: string Lizard: allOf: - $ref: '#/components/schemas/Pet' - type: object # all other properties specific to a \`Lizard\` properties: lovesRocks: type: boolean</span></span>
